'''Cho Wi-je''' ({{Korean|조위제}}; born 25 August 2001) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kleague.com/record/playerDetail.do?playerId=20220174 |title=Profile |accessdate=31 May 2026 |publisher=kleague.com |language=Korean}}</ref>

==Club career==
In 2021, Cho Wi-je signed a professional contract with Busan IPark.<ref>{{Cite web |title= 프로축구 부산, 유스팀 출신 조위제 우선 지명 영입|trans-title= Professional football team Busan gives first priority to signing Cho Wi-je, who came from the youth team. |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20211222046100007 |website=Yonhap |date=2021-12-22 |access-date=2021-12-22 |language=ko |last=연합뉴스}}</ref>

Four years later, he received a call from Jeonbuk and joined Jeonbuk in January 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |title= 전북현대모터스FC, ‘철벽’ 센터백 조위제 합류… 수비 라인 세대교체 |trans-title= Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors FC, 'Impenetrable' center back Jo Wi-je joins… Defensive line undergoes generational change |url=https://hyundai-motorsfc.com/media/news/100663 |website=hyundai-motorsfc.com |date=2026-01-07 |access-date=2026-01-07 |language=ko |last=전북현대모터스}}</ref>

==International career==
Cho Wi-je was called up to the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] on 31 May 2026 as a replacement for the injured [[Cho Yu-min]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/south-korea-defender-cho-ruled-out-world-cup-2026-06-01/ |title=South Korea defender Cho ruled out of World Cup |work=[[Reuters]] |date=May 31, 2026 |access-date=June 1, 2026}}</ref>

